WHILE
residents have lost all their belongings in the floods as heavy rains hit
several kasis in Tshwane over the weekend, some had a reason to smile. Solomon
Nkosi (48) saved a toddler who almost drowned in a shack at the Sizanani
informal settlement as water levels rose to dangerous levels.The
kasi in the east of Mamelodi was hammered by heavy rains which flooded shacks
in the area from Thursday evening until Saturday morning, forcing residents to
